Page_0: "If the Fire doth strike the heart, with no thought for the sake of right, then doth the fire make the heart, or the heart make the Fire?

Never a twist or turn, to find a more accomplished fate. Always seeking onward, grasping knowledge in the wake.

But do not be deceived by the fire that burns throughout the land. As I seek thee as thyself, so must thou seek me."

Page_1: "Thou must spend hours upon each day rehearsing the burning scriptures, for the time when thou wilt be called upon to prove thy worth.

T'is always better to have learnt and lost, than to go onward unknown."